data.description: This charming Chicago brick home is truly a special one-of-a-kind, in sought-after north Wheaton. Beautifully updated and spacious at 3700 sq. ft., the crafted vintage windows allow tremendous natural light to shine throughout the main level. As you walk in you see the striking stone floor, and the wow factor of the oversized living room with textured walls, vaulted barrel ceiling, and stunning fireplace-all that make this home perfect for gatherings, entertaining, or cozy nights. The dining room has a unique plaster and wood tray ceiling, built-in lighted cabinet, and vintage windows that provide endless sunlight. The eating nook is cozy, and the kitchen is large with ample cherry cabinet space, triple sink, and stainless-steel appliances (10/2022). Main floor also has the primary bedroom, beautifully updated main bath, and second bedroom. Upstairs are two large bedrooms, a fully updated bathroom, and a landing sitting area. Finished basement has additional and highly usable space: A large full family room, recreation or exercise room, laundry and utility room, workroom, full bath, and a bonus room that can be used for an office, playroom, or whatever you would like, so many possibilities! The backyard is beautiful and peaceful-you can sit on the deck and enjoy morning coffee or end-of-day relaxation, while appreciating the stone patio, defined perennial gardens, tiered brick planters, and ornamental trees-all enclosed by a full cedar privacy fence. As you walk through this charming property, the care and maintenance are obvious! The many updates have been lovingly made to keep it in tip top condition-check out the Feature and Updates including the new roof on the home, garage and cedar shed (2023). This home is truly a vintage stunner! North Wheaton is an amazing location that comes with top Wheaton schools, one block from the heart of Wheaton College, less than 1/2 mile walk to the commuter train, Prairie path, downtown Wheaton, local parks, and all that Wheaton has to offer.
